category.name: support
description:
Do you know how to have fun without the need of consuming alcohol or other drugs? 

So do we! 

What are we? A social group formed by people from all over the world (including Sweden!) that are based in Stockholm and enjoy hanging out without taking any kind of alcohol, tobacco or other drugs. 

What are we NOT? A supporting/recovery group (However, if that your case you're of course welcome to join us to have fun and meet new friends). We don't do talks about/against alcohol etc either. For those and other topics you already have AA, IOGT-NTO, and other organizations that will help you better. We are just a social group. 

But... I do drink (some) alcohol, can I still join the group? Sure! The idea of the group is to create a community that enjoy spending its time together without taking alcohol and doing alternative activities. If you can do that you're welcome to join us too! 

What do we do?  Anything! (Usually free of charge or cheap activities)

The meetups can be: picnic, bowling, museum visits, sports, concerts, paintball, board games, cooking, hiking ... or even preparing & sharing alcohol-free drinks!

The main idea is to share our time with new potential friends.

When do we meet? We try to meet once per week, usually on weekends. We could meet more often but we need more organizers! Do you want to be want? Read the question bellow for contact info.

I have some ideas for meetups, how can I share them? Contact me(Magui) through the meetup messages, e-mail (adtfree.meetup@gmail.com) or through our Facebook group.

Can I become an activities organizer? Yes, please, we need you! (Read the question above for contact info)

How can I get in touch with more members or share ideas? Join to our Facebook group for more updates and find more friends.

Nykter nyktra aktiviteter Stockholm Sverige vandring promenad nya vänner kontakter alkoholfri gå ut brädspel middag fika ny i stan konserter musik kulturell museer rökfri drogfri fritid träffa folk möte nyktert socialt liv bio film spel friluftsaktiviteter nykterist alkoholfria aktiviteter sober. träffa nyktra vänner.

category.name: support
description:
So many of us have herpes.

Let's meet up and support each other in an LBGTQ-friendly environment.

The first Meetup will probably be in Stockholm in the autumn of 2017.

If you visit or live in Sweden www.qruiser.com is a good place to start looking for info about gay life :) Unfortunately there is very little info regarding herpes there. So far... the only public club I have seen is the one I started... Genital Herpes... but keep safe on this site as I hope you do on all sites <3


And please remember if you are feeling a little low...

Two thirds of the world population have herpes 1 and one third have herpes 2 (different statistis depending on the source) ....

http://www.who.int/mediacentre/news/releases/2015/herpes/en/

category.name: support
description:
This group is for anyone who's tired of small talk and want to meet like minded people. We can grab a coffee or beer at some quiet place and talk about how we handle situations, how the universe came to be and everything in between.

I understand that meeting probably is one of the last things on an introverts mind but I truly believe that we still need connection from other people. And introversion does not equal shyness!

This group also take privacy seriously. That's why content is hidden from non members.


Den här gruppen är till för alla som är trötta på småprat och vill träffa likasinnade personer. Vi kan ta en kaffe eller öl på ett lugnt ställe och prata om hur vi hanterar situationer, hur universum funkar och allt där emellan.

Jag förstår att träffas antagligen är bland det sista en introvert tänker på men jag tror starkt på att vi har ett behov av att känna samhörighet med andra. Och introversion är inte synonymt med blyghet!

Den här gruppen tar privatlivet på allvar. Därför är information i gruppen gömd för ickemedlemmar.

category.name: support
description: If you suffer from social anxiety, you worry a lot about what other people think of you, which is what is holding you back from doing things you really wanna do. It is difficult for you to let your true personality out (which I bet is awesome) because of this great fear you have. You might start shaking, blushing, feel your heart beat faster in your chest, and think everybody is staring and judging you. This Meetup group is for all of us struggling with this, but who wish to overcome it! We'll be a group of people who completely understand each other's feelings, which is a great foundation for creating a comfortable atmosphere and good friendships. In this group we'll try to overcome all the things that are hard for us to do, such as talking to strangers, eating in front of others and other things that we find difficult. Don't worry, we'll take it all in small steps so it'll be comfortable for everyone! - This group is supposed to be fun, and is not about pressuring anybody to do something they really don't wanna do.
name: Copenhagen Social Anxiety Group
organizer.name: Rikke Møller Koblauch

category.name: support
description:
Da jeg boede i USA, var jeg med i en Meetup gruppe for voksne med ADHD, hvor vi mødtes jævnligt på Starbucks, rundt omkring i Los Angeles og hyggede os med at ‘bare være os selv’, drøfte vores glæder og sorger, lærer af hinanden og ikke mindst grine af hinanden og vores f.....d up hjerne og alt det sjov det også giver.

Da vi jo ikke har en forening for voksne med ADHD, endnu, så er her første skridt fra min side. Følg mig på FB på ADDspeaker og/eller på ADDspeaker.net, hvor jeg ‘revser’ samfundet med fokus på ADHD, jævnligt.

Ses vi? Det håber jeg :-)

/Peter ‘ADDspeaker’ Vang
name: ADDspeaker LIVE - For voksne med ADHD

Den här gruppen är till för alla som är trötta på småprat och vill träffa likasinnade personer. Vi kan ta en kaffe eller öl på ett lugnt ställe och prata om hur vi hanterar situationer, hur universum funkar och allt där emellan.

Jag förstår att träffas antagligen är bland det sista en introvert tänker på men jag tror starkt på att vi har ett behov av att känna samhörighet med andra. Och introversion är inte synonymt med blyghet!

Den här gruppen tar privatlivet på allvar. Därför är information i gruppen gömd för ickemedlemmar.

category.name: support
description:
Do you know how to have fun without the need of consuming alcohol or other drugs? 

So do we! 

What are we? A social group formed by people from all over the world (including Sweden!) that are based in Stockholm and enjoy hanging out without taking any kind of alcohol, tobacco or other drugs. 

What are we NOT? A supporting/recovery group (However, if that your case you're of course welcome to join us to have fun and meet new friends). We don't do talks about/against alcohol etc either. For those and other topics you already have AA, IOGT-NTO, and other organizations that will help you better. We are just a social group. 

But... I do drink (some) alcohol, can I still join the group? Sure! The idea of the group is to create a community that enjoy spending its time together without taking alcohol and doing alternative activities. If you can do that you're welcome to join us too! 

What do we do?  Anything! (Usually free of charge or cheap activities)

The meetups can be: picnic, bowling, museum visits, sports, concerts, paintball, board games, cooking, hiking ... or even preparing & sharing alcohol-free drinks!

The main idea is to share our time with new potential friends.

When do we meet? We try to meet once per week, usually on weekends. We could meet more often but we need more organizers! Do you want to be want? Read the question bellow for contact info.

I have some ideas for meetups, how can I share them? Contact me(Magui) through the meetup messages, e-mail (adtfree.meetup@gmail.com) or through our Facebook group.

Can I become an activities organizer? Yes, please, we need you! (Read the question above for contact info)

How can I get in touch with more members or share ideas? Join to our Facebook group for more updates and find more friends.

Two thirds of the world population have herpes 1 and one third have herpes 2 (different statistis depending on the source) ....

category.name: support
description: If you suffer from social anxiety, you worry a lot about what other people think of you, which is what is holding you back from doing things you really wanna do. It is difficult for you to let your true personality out (which I bet is awesome) because of this great fear you have. You might start shaking, blushing, feel your heart beat faster in your chest, and think everybody is staring and judging you. This Meetup group is for all of us struggling with this, but who wish to overcome it! We'll be a group of people who completely understand each other's feelings, which is a great foundation for creating a comfortable atmosphere and good friendships. In this group we'll try to overcome all the things that are hard for us to do, such as talking to strangers, eating in front of others and other things that we find difficult. Don't worry, we'll take it all in small steps so it'll be comfortable for everyone! - This group is supposed to be fun, and is not about pressuring anybody to do something they really don't wanna do.
name: Copenhagen Social Anxiety Group

category.name: support
description:
Da jeg boede i USA, var jeg med i en Meetup gruppe for voksne med ADHD, hvor vi mødtes jævnligt på Starbucks, rundt omkring i Los Angeles og hyggede os med at ‘bare være os selv’, drøfte vores glæder og sorger, lærer af hinanden og ikke mindst grine af hinanden og vores f.....d up hjerne og alt det sjov det også giver.

Da vi jo ikke har en forening for voksne med ADHD, endnu, så er her første skridt fra min side. Følg mig på FB på ADDspeaker og/eller på ADDspeaker.net, hvor jeg ‘revser’ samfundet med fokus på ADHD, jævnligt.

Ses vi? Det håber jeg :-)

category.name: support
description:
Do you know how to have fun without the need of consuming alcohol or other drugs? 

So do we! 

What are we? A social group formed by people from all over the world (including Sweden!) that are based in Stockholm and enjoy hanging out without taking any kind of alcohol, tobacco or other drugs. 

What are we NOT? A supporting/recovery group (However, if that your case you're of course welcome to join us to have fun and meet new friends). We don't do talks about/against alcohol etc either. For those and other topics you already have AA, IOGT-NTO, and other organizations that will help you better. We are just a social group. 

But... I do drink (some) alcohol, can I still join the group? Sure! The idea of the group is to create a community that enjoy spending its time together without taking alcohol and doing alternative activities. If you can do that you're welcome to join us too! 

What do we do?  Anything! (Usually free of charge or cheap activities)

The meetups can be: picnic, bowling, museum visits, sports, concerts, paintball, board games, cooking, hiking ... or even preparing & sharing alcohol-free drinks!

The main idea is to share our time with new potential friends.

When do we meet? We try to meet once per week, usually on weekends. We could meet more often but we need more organizers! Do you want to be want? Read the question bellow for contact info.

I have some ideas for meetups, how can I share them? Contact me(Magui) through the meetup messages, e-mail (adtfree.meetup@gmail.com) or through our Facebook group.

Can I become an activities organizer? Yes, please, we need you! (Read the question above for contact info)

How can I get in touch with more members or share ideas? Join to our Facebook group for more updates and find more friends.

description:
So many of us have herpes.

Let's meet up and support each other in an LBGTQ-friendly environment.

The first Meetup will probably be in Stockholm in the autumn of 2017.

If you visit or live in Sweden www.qruiser.com is a good place to start looking for info about gay life :) Unfortunately there is very little info regarding herpes there. So far... the only public club I have seen is the one I started... Genital Herpes... but keep safe on this site as I hope you do on all sites <3


And please remember if you are feeling a little low...

Two thirds of the world population have herpes 1 and one third have herpes 2 (different statistis depending on the source) ....

category.name: support
description: If you suffer from social anxiety, you worry a lot about what other people think of you, which is what is holding you back from doing things you really wanna do. It is difficult for you to let your true personality out (which I bet is awesome) because of this great fear you have. You might start shaking, blushing, feel your heart beat faster in your chest, and think everybody is staring and judging you. This Meetup group is for all of us struggling with this, but who wish to overcome it! We'll be a group of people who completely understand each other's feelings, which is a great foundation for creating a comfortable atmosphere and good friendships. In this group we'll try to overcome all the things that are hard for us to do, such as talking to strangers, eating in front of others and other things that we find difficult. Don't worry, we'll take it all in small steps so it'll be comfortable for everyone! - This group is supposed to be fun, and is not about pressuring anybody to do something they really don't wanna do.

category.name: support
description:
Da jeg boede i USA, var jeg med i en Meetup gruppe for voksne med ADHD, hvor vi mødtes jævnligt på Starbucks, rundt omkring i Los Angeles og hyggede os med at ‘bare være os selv’, drøfte vores glæder og sorger, lærer af hinanden og ikke mindst grine af hinanden og vores f.....d up hjerne og alt det sjov det også giver.

Da vi jo ikke har en forening for voksne med ADHD, endnu, så er her første skridt fra min side. Følg mig på FB på ADDspeaker og/eller på ADDspeaker.net, hvor jeg ‘revser’ samfundet med fokus på ADHD, jævnligt.

Ses vi? Det håber jeg :-)

/Peter ‘ADDspeaker’ Vang

category.name: support
description:
Do you know how to have fun without the need of consuming alcohol or other drugs? 

So do we! 

What are we? A social group formed by people from all over the world (including Sweden!) that are based in Stockholm and enjoy hanging out without taking any kind of alcohol, tobacco or other drugs. 

What are we NOT? A supporting/recovery group (However, if that your case you're of course welcome to join us to have fun and meet new friends). We don't do talks about/against alcohol etc either. For those and other topics you already have AA, IOGT-NTO, and other organizations that will help you better. We are just a social group. 

But... I do drink (some) alcohol, can I still join the group? Sure! The idea of the group is to create a community that enjoy spending its time together without taking alcohol and doing alternative activities. If you can do that you're welcome to join us too! 

What do we do?  Anything! (Usually free of charge or cheap activities)

The meetups can be: picnic, bowling, museum visits, sports, concerts, paintball, board games, cooking, hiking ... or even preparing & sharing alcohol-free drinks!

The main idea is to share our time with new potential friends.

When do we meet? We try to meet once per week, usually on weekends. We could meet more often but we need more organizers! Do you want to be want? Read the question bellow for contact info.

I have some ideas for meetups, how can I share them? Contact me(Magui) through the meetup messages, e-mail (adtfree.meetup@gmail.com) or through our Facebook group.

Can I become an activities organizer? Yes, please, we need you! (Read the question above for contact info)

How can I get in touch with more members or share ideas? Join to our Facebook group for more updates and find more friends.

category.name: support
description:
This group is for anyone who's tired of small talk and want to meet like minded people. We can grab a coffee or beer at some quiet place and talk about how we handle situations, how the universe came to be and everything in between.

I understand that meeting probably is one of the last things on an introverts mind but I truly believe that we still need connection from other people. And introversion does not equal shyness!

This group also take privacy seriously. That's why content is hidden from non members.


Den här gruppen är till för alla som är trötta på småprat och vill träffa likasinnade personer. Vi kan ta en kaffe eller öl på ett lugnt ställe och prata om hur vi hanterar situationer, hur universum funkar och allt där emellan.

Jag förstår att träffas antagligen är bland det sista en introvert tänker på men jag tror starkt på att vi har ett behov av att känna samhörighet med andra. Och introversion är inte synonymt med blyghet!

This group also take privacy seriously. That's why content is hidden from non members.

category.name: support
description:
Do you know how to have fun without the need of consuming alcohol or other drugs? 

So do we! 

What are we? A social group formed by people from all over the world (including Sweden!) that are based in Stockholm and enjoy hanging out without taking any kind of alcohol, tobacco or other drugs. 

What are we NOT? A supporting/recovery group (However, if that your case you're of course welcome to join us to have fun and meet new friends). We don't do talks about/against alcohol etc either. For those and other topics you already have AA, IOGT-NTO, and other organizations that will help you better. We are just a social group. 

But... I do drink (some) alcohol, can I still join the group? Sure! The idea of the group is to create a community that enjoy spending its time together without taking alcohol and doing alternative activities. If you can do that you're welcome to join us too! 

What do we do?  Anything! (Usually free of charge or cheap activities)

The meetups can be: picnic, bowling, museum visits, sports, concerts, paintball, board games, cooking, hiking ... or even preparing & sharing alcohol-free drinks!

The main idea is to share our time with new potential friends.

When do we meet? We try to meet once per week, usually on weekends. We could meet more often but we need more organizers! Do you want to be want? Read the question bellow for contact info.

I have some ideas for meetups, how can I share them? Contact me(Magui) through the meetup messages, e-mail (adtfree.meetup@gmail.com) or through our Facebook group.

Can I become an activities organizer? Yes, please, we need you! (Read the question above for contact info)

How can I get in touch with more members or share ideas? Join to our Facebook group for more updates and find more friends.

description:
So many of us have herpes.

Let's meet up and support each other in an LBGTQ-friendly environment.

The first Meetup will probably be in Stockholm in the autumn of 2017.

If you visit or live in Sweden www.qruiser.com is a good place to start looking for info about gay life :) Unfortunately there is very little info regarding herpes there. So far... the only public club I have seen is the one I started... Genital Herpes... but keep safe on this site as I hope you do on all sites <3


And please remember if you are feeling a little low...

Two thirds of the world population have herpes 1 and one third have herpes 2 (different statistis depending on the source) ....

category.name: support
description: If you suffer from social anxiety, you worry a lot about what other people think of you, which is what is holding you back from doing things you really wanna do. It is difficult for you to let your true personality out (which I bet is awesome) because of this great fear you have. You might start shaking, blushing, feel your heart beat faster in your chest, and think everybody is staring and judging you. This Meetup group is for all of us struggling with this, but who wish to overcome it! We'll be a group of people who completely understand each other's feelings, which is a great foundation for creating a comfortable atmosphere and good friendships. In this group we'll try to overcome all the things that are hard for us to do, such as talking to strangers, eating in front of others and other things that we find difficult. Don't worry, we'll take it all in small steps so it'll be comfortable for everyone! - This group is supposed to be fun, and is not about pressuring anybody to do something they really don't wanna do.
name: Copenhagen Social Anxiety Group

category.name: support
description:
Da jeg boede i USA, var jeg med i en Meetup gruppe for voksne med ADHD, hvor vi mødtes jævnligt på Starbucks, rundt omkring i Los Angeles og hyggede os med at ‘bare være os selv’, drøfte vores glæder og sorger, lærer af hinanden og ikke mindst grine af hinanden og vores f.....d up hjerne og alt det sjov det også giver.

Da vi jo ikke har en forening for voksne med ADHD, endnu, så er her første skridt fra min side. Følg mig på FB på ADDspeaker og/eller på ADDspeaker.net, hvor jeg ‘revser’ samfundet med fokus på ADHD, jævnligt.

Ses vi? Det håber jeg :-)

/Peter ‘ADDspeaker’ Vang
name: ADDspeaker LIVE - For voksne med ADHD
